text: Nellie Elizabeth McCalla (also Irish McCalla; December 25, 1928 â€“ February 1, 2002) was an American actress and artist. She was best known for playing the title character in Sheena, Queen of the Jungle. She also played Marie Baron in The Beat Generation. She was born in Pawnee City, Nebraska. She died from a stroke and brain tumors, age 73.
